The paper presents a mechanism design for a double auction, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism is also based on random-sampling and posted pricing, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the gain-from-trade and budget-balancing properties of the mechanism, which are topics in economics and finance (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to prove the properties of the mechanism, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
